Nigerian Bottling Climbs to 3-Month High, Raises Cancel Premium

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-06-09T14:13:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/nigerian-bottling-climbs-to-3-month-high-raises-cancel-premium.html
Nigerian Bottling Company Plc, which
bottles Coca-Cola Co. products, rose to a three-month high after
saying it will increase the premium it will pay for shares as
part of plans to delist from the nation’s bourse.  The stock gained 1.86 naira, or 5 percent, to 39.13 naira
by the 2:30 p.m. close in Lagos, the highest since March 1.  Nigerian Bottling will pay 47 naira for each canceled
share, up from 43 naira per share it announced on Dec. 13, the
Lagos-based company said in a statement on the website of the
 Nigerian Stock Exchange .  The company plans to cancel part of the paid-up share
capital and subsequently delist from the Nigerian Stock
Exchange, it said in a statement on the Lagos-based bourse’s
website today. The transaction is subject to approval of
shareholders at a meeting ordered by the Federal High Court,
according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
